WEBVTT

1
00:03:11.508 --> 00:03:13.116
How did you get him
so quickly?


2
00:03:13.116 --> 00:03:15.201
A medical team heard
the shell coming in.


3
00:03:15.201 --> 00:03:16.765
Apparently, he did, too.

4
00:03:17.286 --> 00:03:19.763
Chest and belly
practically unmarked.


5
00:03:19.763 --> 00:03:22.239
Curious how they always
double up in the fetal position.


6
00:03:22.239 --> 00:03:23.760
What's curious about it?

7
00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:25.673
They're trying to
protect their genitals.


8
00:03:25.673 --> 00:03:28.670
Well, this young man
unfortunately succeeded.


9
00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:30.626
Any identification?

10
00:03:30.626 --> 00:03:31.710
No, sir.

11
00:03:31.710 --> 00:03:33.057
Then we'll assume he's ours.

12
00:03:33.623 --> 00:03:36.142
I'll need to take personal
charge of this case


13
00:03:36.142 --> 00:03:37.663
until repairs are completed.

14
00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:39.705
That could be
rather a long time,


15
00:03:39.705 --> 00:03:41.270
Colonel Tillery.

16
00:03:41.270 --> 00:03:42.788
Wouldn't you say, Captain,

17
00:03:42.788 --> 00:03:44.832
that it's worth a year
of any doctor's life


18
00:03:44.832 --> 00:03:46.700
to observe
a case like this?


19
00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:49.785
You'd never know what
has happened to him.


20
00:03:49.785 --> 00:03:52.392
The one part of his brain
that has escaped damage


21
00:03:52.392 --> 00:03:54.478
is the medulla oblongata.

22
00:03:54.478 --> 00:03:56.562
It is only because of this

23
00:03:56.562 --> 00:03:58.648
that his heart, vasal, motor,

24
00:03:58.648 --> 00:04:01.255
and respiratory centers
still function.


25
00:04:01.255 --> 00:04:04.382
In short, that he lives.

26
00:05:10.160 --> 00:05:13.288
Unidentified casualty
number 4-7.


27
00:05:13.288 --> 00:05:15.374
Post-operation orders,

28
00:05:15.374 --> 00:05:16.417
Colonel M.F. Tillery,

29
00:05:16.417 --> 00:05:19.023
U.S. Army Medical Corps.

30
00:05:19.023 --> 00:05:21.630
Although the cerebellum
still permits


31
00:05:21.630 --> 00:05:23.194
limited physical movement,

32
00:05:23.194 --> 00:05:25.801
said movement
signifies nothing.


33
00:05:25.801 --> 00:05:28.407
Bodily actions
have become violent,


34
00:05:28.929 --> 00:05:29.971
and are persistently
repetitive


35
00:05:30.493 --> 00:05:33.621
and must be treated as
reflexive muscular spasms--


36
00:05:33.621 --> 00:05:36.227
which is to say, by sedation.

37
00:05:39.226 --> 00:05:43.396
The cerebrum has suffered
massive and irreparable damage.


38
00:05:43.396 --> 00:05:44.960
Had I not been sure of this,

39
00:05:44.960 --> 00:05:48.088
I would not have
permitted him to live.


40
00:05:51.738 --> 00:05:55.953
There's no justification
for his continued existence


41
00:05:55.953 --> 00:05:59.038
unless we learn from him
how to help others.


42
00:05:59.038 --> 00:06:01.122
Care for him as gently

43
00:06:01.644 --> 00:06:03.207
as if he knew
what you were doing


44
00:06:03.207 --> 00:06:06.336
and would feel the pain
if you did it badly.


45
00:06:06.336 --> 00:06:08.943
Attending personnel
will remember that


46
00:06:08.943 --> 00:06:10.462
good medical care forbids

47
00:06:10.462 --> 00:06:13.330
emotional involvement
with the patient.


48
00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:16.373
Avoid such involvement
by remembering


49
00:06:16.373 --> 00:06:19.500
that it is impossible for
a decerebrated individual


50
00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:23.149
to experience pain,
pleasure, memory,


51
00:06:23.149 --> 00:06:26.756
dreams, or thought
of any kind.


52
00:06:26.756 --> 00:06:29.883
It follows, therefore,
that this young man


53
00:06:29.883 --> 00:06:33.533
will be as unfeeling,
as unthinking as the dead


54
00:06:33.533 --> 00:06:36.140
until the day he joins them.

55
00:06:56.733 --> 00:06:58.818
Kareen?

56
00:07:05.596 --> 00:07:07.161
Kareen?

57
00:07:11.331 --> 00:07:13.938
What happened?

58
00:07:16.067 --> 00:07:18.152
Where am I?

59
00:07:24.409 --> 00:07:27.015
It's dark in here.

60
00:07:29.101 --> 00:07:30.144
Shouldn't have
turned the lights out.


61
00:07:30.144 --> 00:07:32.229
Your old man
will be sore.


62
00:07:32.229 --> 00:07:34.140
Oh, Mike won't care.
He loves me.


63
00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:37.920
Only could I just
ask you one thing?


64
00:07:38.442 --> 00:07:40.485
Why'd you have to volunteer?

65
00:07:40.485 --> 00:07:43.003
Only six months
from the draft anyhow.


66
00:07:43.003 --> 00:07:45.610
Pinkie and Larry
have already gone.


67
00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:48.218
You could have been exempt
because of your sisters.


68
00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:49.781
My mother's got a job.

69
00:07:49.781 --> 00:07:51.215
Besides, when the country
needs you, you've gotta go.


70
00:07:51.215 --> 00:07:53.214
You should go.

71
00:07:53.214 --> 00:07:55.865
I don't think
anybody should go.


72
00:07:55.865 --> 00:07:57.861
They'll kill you.

73
00:07:57.861 --> 00:07:59.947
Oh, I could get killed
at the bakery, too,


74
00:07:59.947 --> 00:08:02.033
or crossing the street.

75
00:08:02.033 --> 00:08:05.160
I can take care of myself.
Don't worry.


76
00:08:05.160 --> 00:08:08.202
Lots of people get killed
who don't think they'll be.


77
00:08:08.202 --> 00:08:10.201
Lots of people come
back, too. Most of 'em.


78
00:08:10.201 --> 00:08:14.111
Most of them, Joe,
they never come back.


79
00:08:14.111 --> 00:08:16.023
Oh, if anything ever
happened to you,


80
00:08:16.023 --> 00:08:17.501
I'd just die.

81
00:08:17.501 --> 00:08:20.410
Ah, you're only
saying that.


82
00:08:21.454 --> 00:08:23.451
I love you.

83
00:08:23.451 --> 00:08:25.537
I do love you.

84
00:08:37.224 --> 00:08:38.788
Stop it.

85
00:08:40.874 --> 00:08:42.959
I won't have this
in my house.


86
00:08:42.959 --> 00:08:44.871
You think you're sitting in
the back seat of a flivver?


87
00:08:44.871 --> 00:08:47.217
Now get up. Both of you,
get up like decent people.


88
00:08:47.217 --> 00:08:48.781
Come on, get up.

89
00:08:48.781 --> 00:08:50.346
But he's going away
in the morning.


90
00:08:50.867 --> 00:08:52.953
I know, I know.
Get in the bedroom.


91
00:08:53.994 --> 00:08:55.559
Both of you.

92
00:09:02.684 --> 00:09:04.248
I ain't much.

93
00:09:04.770 --> 00:09:06.333
25 years
in the coal mines,


94
00:09:06.333 --> 00:09:07.898
carryin' an IWW card.

95
00:09:07.898 --> 00:09:09.287
Now, what am I?

96
00:09:09.287 --> 00:09:11.330
Goddamn railroad
bull, that's what.


97
00:09:11.330 --> 00:09:13.371
Oh, anyhow.

98
00:09:13.371 --> 00:09:15.413
Go on in there
with her. She's scared.


99
00:09:15.413 --> 00:09:17.413
Go-
- Go on in.

100
00:09:17.413 --> 00:09:19.280
Yes, sir.
Put your arms around her.


101
00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:21.366
You know how to
treat her, don't you? Yes, sir.


102
00:09:21.366 --> 00:09:22.887
Uh--

103
00:09:22.887 --> 00:09:24.928
She isn't a whore.
You know that, don't ya?


104
00:09:24.928 --> 00:09:26.492
Yes, sir.

105
00:09:26.492 --> 00:09:29.056
Eh, go to bed, son.

106
00:09:29.056 --> 00:09:30.621
Yes, sir.

107
00:09:37.832 --> 00:09:39.873
Son.

108
00:09:46.043 --> 00:09:47.998
I see you.

109
00:09:49.562 --> 00:09:51.127
Nice room.

110
00:09:55.166 --> 00:09:58.208
Mike fixed it up
for my graduation.


111
00:10:00.815 --> 00:10:03.248
Picture's crooked, though.

112
00:10:09.331 --> 00:10:11.242
It was my mother's.

113
00:10:17.454 --> 00:10:19.497
Why don't you
take your shoes off?


114
00:10:19.497 --> 00:10:21.018
Okay.

115
00:11:08.678 --> 00:11:09.765
Joe.

116
00:11:10.199 --> 00:11:11.241
Yeah?

117
00:11:11.241 --> 00:11:12.806
Could you turn your back?

118
00:11:12.806 --> 00:11:14.370
Why?

119
00:11:14.370 --> 00:11:15.846
I have to get out of bed.

120
00:11:15.846 --> 00:11:18.757
No. I want to see you.

121
00:11:18.757 --> 00:11:20.322
I won't let you see me.

122
00:11:20.322 --> 00:11:22.277
Would you get me my robe?

123
00:11:22.277 --> 00:11:23.145
Sure.

124
00:11:23.536 --> 00:11:25.189
It's on the closet
door. It's red.


125
00:11:26.577 --> 00:11:28.488
Okay.

126
00:11:35.615 --> 00:11:37.701
Why'd you do that?

127
00:11:37.701 --> 00:11:39.743
Hot night.

128
00:11:39.743 --> 00:11:40.654
Here it is.

129
00:11:41.175 --> 00:11:45.173
Bring it
closer, silly. Uh-uh. Reach for it.


130
00:11:45.173 --> 00:11:47.257
All right, here.
I'll help you.


131
00:11:54.513 --> 00:11:56.599
Oops.

132
00:12:00.076 --> 00:12:02.160
Let's get it
through here.


133
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:05.202
There. There you go.

134
00:12:07.287 --> 00:12:09.850
I'll get it right.

135
00:12:09.850 --> 00:12:10.893
Here, let me show you.

136
00:12:10.893 --> 00:12:14.021
Now we got it. There.

137
00:12:16.106 --> 00:12:18.627
Huh?
No.


138
00:12:46.345 --> 00:12:49.387
We should have flowers.
Hm? Sure.


139
00:12:56.816 --> 00:12:59.423
If you really
want to see me--


140
00:12:59.423 --> 00:13:00.987
Oh, if you don't
want me to,


141
00:13:00.987 --> 00:13:02.550
I don't want to, either.

142
00:13:47.561 --> 00:13:50.167
Well, fair is fair.

143
00:13:56.901 --> 00:13:59.378
Okay.

144
00:15:30.702 --> 00:15:32.267
It's nice like this,
isn't it?


145
00:15:32.267 --> 00:15:35.220
Mm-hmm.

146
00:15:35.220 --> 00:15:37.827
Have you ever been this
way with anyone else?


147
00:15:37.827 --> 00:15:39.913
Not with anyone I loved.

148
00:15:40.390 --> 00:15:41.955
I'm glad.

149
00:15:42.476 --> 00:15:44.040
Have you?

150
00:15:44.083 --> 00:15:45.647
You shouldn't
ask that.


151
00:15:45.647 --> 00:15:47.169
Why not?

152
00:15:47.690 --> 00:15:48.688
Because I'm a lady.

153
00:15:48.688 --> 00:15:51.643
You're a mick.

154
00:15:51.643 --> 00:15:53.164
No, I've never
been this way


155
00:15:53.164 --> 00:15:55.206
with anyone
else before.


156
00:15:55.206 --> 00:15:57.813
I know.
But you couldn't have known.


157
00:15:57.813 --> 00:15:59.376
Not really.

158
00:15:59.376 --> 00:16:03.373
Joe, I don't
want you to go.


159
00:16:03.373 --> 00:16:06.458
I want you
to run away.


160
00:16:06.458 --> 00:16:09.021
You don't want me
to see Paris, France,


161
00:16:09.021 --> 00:16:10.586
that's all.

162
00:16:21.794 --> 00:16:24.358
Don't go, Joe.
Please don't go.


163
00:16:24.358 --> 00:16:26.747
Run away.

164
00:16:26.747 --> 00:16:27.791
Where to? Shipyards?

165
00:16:28.312 --> 00:16:29.789
Anywhere.

166
00:16:29.789 --> 00:16:31.614
I'll hide you,
honest I will.


167
00:16:32.135 --> 00:16:34.567
Want me to be
a slacker, huh?


168
00:16:34.567 --> 00:16:36.002
Yes.

169
00:16:36.002 --> 00:16:39.347
Oh, they'll kill you,
Joe. I know they will.


170
00:16:39.347 --> 00:16:42.474
In the words of
that great patriot


171
00:16:42.474 --> 00:16:44.517
Theodore Roosevelt--

172
00:16:44.517 --> 00:16:46.559
I love you, Joe.

173
00:16:46.559 --> 00:16:49.556
Hold me closer.

174
00:16:49.556 --> 00:16:52.163
Put both your arms
around me.


175
00:16:52.163 --> 00:16:54.163
Both of them.

176
00:16:59.723 --> 00:17:01.808
Let us pray.

177
00:17:04.285 --> 00:17:05.328
Our Father--

178
00:17:09.021 --> 00:17:12.105
I can't pray like that.

179
00:17:12.105 --> 00:17:14.016
All I can say is
dear God,


180
00:17:14.451 --> 00:17:16.363
don't make him go away.

181
00:17:16.363 --> 00:17:18.883
Don't let him be killed.
I won't be.


182
00:17:18.883 --> 00:17:21.968
All aboard!

183
00:17:23.922 --> 00:17:25.009
All aboard!

184
00:18:44.602 --> 00:18:46.645
<i>Why don't they turn the lights on?</i>

185
00:18:49.468 --> 00:18:51.033
<i>It's dark in here.</i>

186
00:18:54.074 --> 00:18:56.681
<i>It's dark and still,</i>

187
00:18:56.681 --> 00:19:01.285
<i>and I can feel the blood
pumping through my veins.</i>


188
00:19:01.285 --> 00:19:04.240
<i>But I can't hear
the pulse in my ears.</i>


189
00:19:07.324 --> 00:19:09.324
<i>If you can't hear
your own pulse, you're deaf.</i>


190
00:19:09.845 --> 00:19:11.409
<i>You're deaf, Joe.</i>

191
00:19:11.409 --> 00:19:13.451
<i>Deaf.</i>

192
00:19:15.318 --> 00:19:18.925
<i>Maybe not.
Maybe I'm just dreaming.</i>


193
00:19:18.925 --> 00:19:21.401
<i>Maybe-- oh, Jesus
Christ, I hurt!</i>


194
00:19:24.964 --> 00:19:29.656
<i>I can feel the sweat
pouring out of my skin.</i>


195
00:19:29.656 --> 00:19:32.741
<i>Hot, wet skin that's
all covered up with--</i>


196
00:19:33.175 --> 00:19:35.173
<i>with bandages.</i>

197
00:19:35.173 --> 00:19:37.563
<i>Even my head.</i>

198
00:19:37.563 --> 00:19:40.474
<i>I sure must've
caught a big one.</i>


199
00:19:42.516 --> 00:19:44.036
<i>No.</i>

200
00:19:44.036 --> 00:19:46.079
<i>Telephones in the middle
of the night</i>


201
00:19:46.079 --> 00:19:47.599
<i>are bad luck.</i>

202
00:19:47.599 --> 00:19:50.553
<i>Don't let anybody
answer it, Father.</i>


203
00:19:52.639 --> 00:19:54.725
<i>What's this? 
Footsteps.</i>

204
00:19:54.725 --> 00:19:57.331
<i>I can feel
their vibrations.</i>


205
00:20:04.021 --> 00:20:05.890
<i>What are they doing?</i>

206
00:20:07.455 --> 00:20:09.540
Any evidence of
hypostasis


207
00:20:09.540 --> 00:20:10.582
while aspirating?

208
00:20:11.104 --> 00:20:12.581
None thus far.

209
00:20:18.836 --> 00:20:20.922
<i>They're looking
at something.</i>


210
00:20:20.922 --> 00:20:22.487
Trachea tube clear.

211
00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:26.440
<i>A hand on my chest.</i>

212
00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:28.048
He's breathing well.

213
00:20:30.655 --> 00:20:33.783
No more oxygen unless
an emergency develops.


214
00:20:35.868 --> 00:20:37.433
<i>I don't understand that.</i>

215
00:20:37.433 --> 00:20:39.429
Can you lift for
intravenous feeling?


216
00:20:39.429 --> 00:20:40.951
Good.

217
00:20:43.037 --> 00:20:44.601
<i>My face.</i>

218
00:20:44.601 --> 00:20:46.077
<i>Is something wrong
with my face?</i>


219
00:20:46.077 --> 00:20:47.599
Skin grafts will
be necessary here.


220
00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:51.726
Colostomy good.

221
00:20:51.726 --> 00:20:54.202
Cystotomy functioning?

222
00:20:54.202 --> 00:20:55.767
Uh-huh.
Very good.


223
00:20:55.767 --> 00:20:56.723
<i>What next?</i>

224
00:20:56.723 --> 00:20:58.286
Is the ambulance
ready? Yes, sir.


225
00:20:58.286 --> 00:20:59.850
Very well.
Bring him along.


226
00:20:59.850 --> 00:21:01.936
Where are you
taking him, sir?


227
00:21:01.936 --> 00:21:04.455
Occupation forces
base hospital


228
00:21:04.455 --> 00:21:06.889
number 3 at
Jeanville St. Clears.


229
00:21:09.496 --> 00:21:12.623
All right.
Let's move it.


230
00:21:12.623 --> 00:21:13.709
<i>David's Perfection Bakery.</i>

231
00:21:13.709 --> 00:21:14.752
<i>Rudy McKenna speaking.</i>

232
00:21:14.752 --> 00:21:16.316
<i>It's Rudy.</i>

233
00:21:16.316 --> 00:21:17.359
<i>Telephone, Joe.</i>

234
00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:18.923
<i>Okay, coming.</i>

235
00:21:24.136 --> 00:21:25.615
Hello.

236
00:21:32.565 --> 00:21:35.476
Yes, Mother.
I'll be right home.


237
00:21:46.382 --> 00:21:48.293
Thank you.
I'll let you know


238
00:21:48.336 --> 00:21:50.422
when everything's
finished, okay? Okay, Joe.


239
00:21:50.943 --> 00:21:52.507
I'll be back to work
in a couple days.


240
00:21:52.507 --> 00:21:56.026
That's all right.
Rest up. Good night.


241
00:24:12.795 --> 00:24:15.401
I'm sorry, Father.

242
00:24:16.965 --> 00:24:20.137
I'm sorry I lost
your fishing pole, too.


243
00:24:22.179 --> 00:24:24.264
I loved you.

244
00:24:38.255 --> 00:24:41.382
<i>Well, the bandages
are off my arm.</i>


245
00:24:41.904 --> 00:24:43.468
<i>It itches.</i>

246
00:24:43.468 --> 00:24:45.553
<i>I wish they'd
scratch it.</i>


247
00:24:47.639 --> 00:24:48.681
<i>What happens now?</i>

248
00:24:48.681 --> 00:24:51.201
Yes, we can remove
the sutures.


249
00:24:51.201 --> 00:24:54.372
Let's disinfect.

250
00:24:54.372 --> 00:24:56.458
<i>I wish they'd get
this stuff off my face</i>


251
00:24:56.458 --> 00:24:58.543
<i>so I could see
what they're doing.</i>


252
00:24:58.543 --> 00:25:00.108
Sorry, sir.
Another.


253
00:25:10.448 --> 00:25:11.925
<i>Ouch!</i>

254
00:25:11.925 --> 00:25:12.924
<i>They're pinching me.</i>

255
00:25:12.924 --> 00:25:15.445
<i>No, it's more like a--</i>

256
00:25:15.445 --> 00:25:18.485
<i>a little stab of heat.</i>

257
00:25:18.485 --> 00:25:20.528
<i>Wait a minute.
I know.</i>


258
00:25:20.528 --> 00:25:21.962
