tell me just one thing.


746
00:50:28.024 --> 00:50:30.631
Are you and I
really here together?


747
00:50:31.152 --> 00:50:32.759
Or is this
a dream, too?


748
00:50:32.759 --> 00:50:34.323
It's a dream.
How do you know?


749
00:50:34.323 --> 00:50:37.494
Because I'm a dream.
I don't believe you.


750
00:50:37.494 --> 00:50:40.579
Nobody does.

751
00:50:40.579 --> 00:50:43.099
That's why I'm as unreal

752
00:50:43.099 --> 00:50:46.098
as every other dream
that didn't come true.


753
00:50:51.486 --> 00:50:53.048
<i>I don't know whether
I'm alive and dreaming</i>


754
00:50:53.048 --> 00:50:55.090
<i>or dead and remembering.</i>

755
00:50:55.090 --> 00:50:57.090
<i>Am I getting old?</i>

756
00:50:57.090 --> 00:50:58.654
<i>Is my hair turning gray?</i>

757
00:50:58.654 --> 00:51:01.260
<i>Will anybody ever
come to visit me?</i>


758
00:51:01.782 --> 00:51:03.172
<i>I hope not.</i>

759
00:51:03.172 --> 00:51:04.649
<i>I really wouldn't
want anybody</i>


760
00:51:04.649 --> 00:51:07.126
<i>to see me like this.</i>

761
00:51:07.126 --> 00:51:10.123
<i>I do get homesick, though.</i>

762
00:51:10.123 --> 00:51:12.730
<i>Oh, but they wouldn't
have shipped me that long way home.</i>


763
00:51:12.730 --> 00:51:15.337
<i>Not with all these
tubes and things in me.</i>


764
00:51:15.858 --> 00:51:18.464
<i>No, I'm probably in
some frog hospital,</i>


765
00:51:18.464 --> 00:51:20.550
<i>or maybe limey.</i>

766
00:51:20.550 --> 00:51:23.157
<i>At least my teeth
don't ache.</i>


767
00:51:24.157 --> 00:51:26.719
<i>Wait a minute.
What's this?</i>


768
00:51:26.719 --> 00:51:28.283
<i>There are two
vibrations,</i>


769
00:51:28.283 --> 00:51:29.805
<i>and one of them
is heavy.</i>


770
00:51:29.805 --> 00:51:31.368
<i>It's a man.</i>

771
00:51:31.411 --> 00:51:34.409
Why are the shutters
closed?


772
00:51:34.409 --> 00:51:35.495
They always have been.

773
00:51:36.017 --> 00:51:38.016
At least, as long
as I've been here.


774
00:51:38.016 --> 00:51:40.101
It's on the order sheet.

775
00:51:40.101 --> 00:51:41.621
Well, it's crazy.

776
00:51:41.621 --> 00:51:44.228
<i>Well,
what are you doing?</i>


777
00:51:44.228 --> 00:51:46.314
<i>Hello? Have I
got visitors?</i>


778
00:51:46.314 --> 00:51:47.878
<i>What happened then?</i>

779
00:51:47.878 --> 00:51:49.442
As long as I'm
head nurse of this ward,


780
00:51:49.442 --> 00:51:52.396
the shutters are open
and they will stay open.


781
00:51:52.396 --> 00:51:54.308
Let him have
a little sunshine.


782
00:51:54.308 --> 00:51:55.785
They said it was
to keep people


783
00:51:55.785 --> 00:51:56.785
from peeking
in at him.


784
00:51:58.391 --> 00:51:59.956
It would take a man

785
00:51:59.956 --> 00:52:02.040
to peek through that window.

786
00:52:02.040 --> 00:52:03.605
Oh, and another thing.

787
00:52:04.126 --> 00:52:05.170
I want sheets
on this bed.


788
00:52:05.560 --> 00:52:07.994
<i>He's walking.
No more blankets.</i>


789
00:52:07.994 --> 00:52:10.036
He can't really
tell the difference, you know.


790
00:52:10.036 --> 00:52:12.034
<i>Now he's stopped.
I can.</i>


791
00:52:16.118 --> 00:52:18.594
Well.

792
00:52:18.594 --> 00:52:22.635
How did the triage officer
ever overlook this one?


793
00:52:26.805 --> 00:52:28.239
<i>He's looking at me.</i>

794
00:52:28.760 --> 00:52:30.195
Poor baby.

795
00:52:35.799 --> 00:52:37.362
<i>No, it's a woman.</i>

796
00:52:37.362 --> 00:52:38.841
<i>Those hands, a fat woman.</i>

797
00:52:38.841 --> 00:52:40.839
<i>That's why I could feel
her footsteps so plain.</i>


798
00:52:40.839 --> 00:52:43.837
Poor-
- Poor baby.

799
00:52:48.224 --> 00:52:49.311
Come on.

800
00:52:58.783 --> 00:53:00.302
<i>That was funny.</i>

801
00:53:00.824 --> 00:53:02.301
<i>What were they doing?
What has happened?</i>


802
00:53:02.301 --> 00:53:03.866
<i>What's different?</i>

803
00:53:04.343 --> 00:53:05.864
<i>Think, Joe.</i>

804
00:53:05.864 --> 00:53:06.907
<i>Think. Use your head.</i>

805
00:53:06.907 --> 00:53:08.949
<i>Feel.
Feel with your scalp</i>


806
00:53:08.949 --> 00:53:10.469
<i>and the skin
on your forehead.</i>


807
00:53:10.469 --> 00:53:11.946
<i>Something has changed.</i>

808
00:53:11.946 --> 00:53:15.030
<i>It was cooler before
she came in than it is now.</i>


809
00:53:15.030 --> 00:53:17.595
<i>What I feel is--
is warmth.</i>


810
00:53:17.985 --> 00:53:19.376
<i>But where does it come from?</i>

811
00:53:19.376 --> 00:53:22.417
<i>Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
Of course.</i>


812
00:53:22.417 --> 00:53:24.503
<i>Oh, my God. 
I see it now.</i>

813
00:53:24.503 --> 00:53:27.066
It-
- It's the sun.

814
00:53:27.066 --> 00:53:29.151
<i>The sun, the sun, the sun.</i>

815
00:53:29.151 --> 00:53:32.495
<i>I found the sun.</i>

816
00:53:32.495 --> 00:53:35.451
<i>Thank you, God.</i>

817
00:53:35.972 --> 00:53:40.186
Thank you. Thank you.

818
00:53:45.400 --> 00:53:47.529
If I never have
anything else,


819
00:53:47.529 --> 00:53:50.656
I'll always have God

820
00:53:50.656 --> 00:53:53.263
and the morning sunlight.

821
00:54:01.257 --> 00:54:02.692
<i>It's night.</i>

822
00:54:02.692 --> 00:54:04.081
<i>If a man can
tell the difference</i>


823
00:54:04.081 --> 00:54:04.950
<i>between day and night,</i>

824
00:54:05.472 --> 00:54:06.428
<i>he's beginning to tell time.</i>

825
00:54:06.428 --> 00:54:08.426
<i>It's warm again.
It's morning,</i>


826
00:54:08.990 --> 00:54:10.425
<i>and she's changing
my sheets.</i>


827
00:54:10.728 --> 00:54:12.293
<i>Now it's night.</i>

828
00:54:12.293 --> 00:54:14.594
<i>Morning again.
She's bathing me.</i>


829
00:54:14.594 --> 00:54:16.116
<i>One morning she changes me,</i>

830
00:54:16.116 --> 00:54:18.028
<i>the next morning,
she bathes me.</i>


831
00:54:18.028 --> 00:54:19.505
<i>Night, night.</i>

832
00:54:19.767 --> 00:54:21.156
<i>Day. Night.</i>

833
00:54:21.503 --> 00:54:22.850
<i>How will I keep track?</i>

834
00:54:23.155 --> 00:54:24.805
<i>I know.
Put a big blackboard up in your mind.</i>


835
00:54:24.805 --> 00:54:26.500
<i>And right here
in the middle,</i>


836
00:54:26.500 --> 00:54:28.151
<i>put a mark for each day.</i>

837
00:54:28.151 --> 00:54:30.670
<i>Four, six, seven days.</i>

838
00:54:30.670 --> 00:54:32.496
<i>Now, put a mark up
in this corner for the weeks.</i>


839
00:54:32.496 --> 00:54:34.625
<i>Erase the days.
Start over again.</i>


840
00:54:34.625 --> 00:54:36.622
<i>Three, four weeks.
That's right!</i>


841
00:54:36.622 --> 00:54:38.057
<i>Erase the weeks
and mark down</i>


842
00:54:38.057 --> 00:54:39.056
<i>a month over here.</i>

843
00:54:39.359 --> 00:54:42.575
<i>5, 9, 11, 12 months.</i>

844
00:54:42.575 --> 00:54:43.531
<i>Now that isn't a year,
not yet.</i>


845
00:54:44.052 --> 00:54:45.182
<i>Four twelves is only 48.</i>

846
00:54:45.182 --> 00:54:47.614
<i>Okay, check off
four more weeks,</i>


847
00:54:47.963 --> 00:54:49.179
<i>very carefully.</i>

848
00:54:49.395 --> 00:54:52.262
<i>And then put Roman
numeral number 1</i>


849
00:54:52.262 --> 00:54:54.827
<i>right down here. One year!</i>

850
00:54:54.827 --> 00:54:56.391
<i>I'm ringing bells!</i>

851
00:54:56.391 --> 00:54:57.868
<i>Hey, I'm blowing horns</i>

852
00:54:57.868 --> 00:54:59.258
<i>and shooting off
firecrackers.</i>


853
00:54:59.258 --> 00:55:00.779
<i>Everybody's singing</i>

854
00:55:00.779 --> 00:55:03.430
<i>"Should old acquaintance
be forgot."</i>


855
00:55:03.430 --> 00:55:05.514
<i>And I'm saying--</i>

856
00:55:05.514 --> 00:55:08.643
<i>I'm saying,
"Happy New Year, Kareen."</i>


857
00:55:08.643 --> 00:55:10.729
<i>And I'm kissing her.</i>

858
00:55:16.724 --> 00:55:19.243
<i>But it isn't
New Year's Day out there.</i>


859
00:55:19.243 --> 00:55:20.807
<i>Sure, I've counted a year,</i>

860
00:55:20.807 --> 00:55:22.806
<i>but a year from when?</i>

861
00:55:22.806 --> 00:55:25.196
<i>I don't even know
how old I am.</i>


862
00:55:25.196 --> 00:55:27.238
<i>All I know is
I'm 20 years old,</i>


863
00:55:27.715 --> 00:55:29.758
<i>plus X years since
I got blown up,</i>


864
00:55:29.758 --> 00:55:32.235
<i>plus the year I just counted.</i>

865
00:55:32.235 --> 00:55:34.753
<i>But when did
those X years begin?</i>


866
00:55:34.753 --> 00:55:37.318
<i>Think, Joe. 
Think back.</i>

867
00:55:37.751 --> 00:55:40.792
<i>We were next to
an English regiment.</i>


868
00:55:40.792 --> 00:55:43.399
<i>And we went out
on night patrol and scattered.</i>


869
00:55:43.399 --> 00:55:44.920
<i>And then I hooked up</i>

870
00:55:44.920 --> 00:55:46.484
<i>with that little
limey corporal</i>


871
00:55:46.484 --> 00:55:47.484
<i>and his outfit, and--</i>

872
00:55:47.484 --> 00:55:50.351
<i>Yes, I remember now.</i>

873
00:55:50.655 --> 00:55:52.740
<i>I was writing a letter
to you, Kareen.</i>


874
00:55:53.219 --> 00:55:54.261
Corporal Timlon?

875
00:55:54.261 --> 00:55:55.825
Yes, sir?

876
00:55:58.953 --> 00:56:02.083
What is that damnable odor?

877
00:56:02.083 --> 00:56:03.124
Out there, sir.

878
00:56:03.645 --> 00:56:06.295
This fat Hun came
stumbling through the fog.


879
00:56:06.295 --> 00:56:09.945
Some bloke lost his head
and popped him off.


880
00:56:09.945 --> 00:56:11.509
The stink ain't half so bad

881
00:56:11.814 --> 00:56:12.726
when they're close
to the ground, sir,


882
00:56:12.726 --> 00:56:14.856
but he's got himself
hung up on the wire.


883
00:56:14.856 --> 00:56:16.897
Bad for morale.
Extremely bad.


884
00:56:16.897 --> 00:56:20.025
He's a Bavarian, sir.
They always smell worse.


885
00:56:20.546 --> 00:56:22.111
Yes, they do,
don't they?


886
00:56:22.632 --> 00:56:25.759
Not so bad as Hindu is,
though. Or Welshmen.


887
00:56:25.759 --> 00:56:27.845
While it's nice and quiet,
sir, we keep on trying


888
00:56:27.845 --> 00:56:29.931
to shoot him down,
but he hangs on pretty good.


889
00:56:29.931 --> 00:56:32.538
Well, take a detail
out tonight, Corporal.


890
00:56:32.538 --> 00:56:34.101
And bury him.

891
00:56:34.101 --> 00:56:36.708
Well, but it's kind of
busy out there, sir. Even at night.


892
00:56:37.229 --> 00:56:39.315
And don't forget,
Corporal.


893
00:56:39.315 --> 00:56:41.922
Death has a dignity
all its own.


894
00:56:41.922 --> 00:56:46.092
And you will say
a few words of prayer over the remains.


895
00:56:46.614 --> 00:56:48.178
Yes.

896
00:56:50.264 --> 00:56:52.348
Oh, Jesus!

897
00:56:52.740 --> 00:56:54.825
Just for that,
I'll take volunteers.


898
00:56:54.825 --> 00:56:56.911
You. You. You.

899
00:56:56.911 --> 00:56:59.430
You two.
You in the back there.


900
00:56:59.430 --> 00:57:01.950
And to almighty God,

901
00:57:01.950 --> 00:57:05.861
we commend the soul of
our brother departed,


902
00:57:05.861 --> 00:57:08.685
and we commit his body
to the ground.


903
00:57:15.374 --> 00:57:19.242
Earth to earth,
ashes to ashes,


904
00:57:19.242 --> 00:57:21.675
dust to dust.

905
00:57:21.675 --> 00:57:23.413
Who's got the dust?

906
00:57:25.410 --> 00:57:27.844
It's kinda wet, but--

907
00:57:27.844 --> 00:57:28.887
I have--

908
00:57:28.887 --> 00:57:33.058
Well, throw the bloody
stuff in. Go on.


909
00:57:36.099 --> 00:57:39.575
Ashes to ashes.
Dust to dust.


910
00:57:39.575 --> 00:57:41.139
God have mercy on his soul!

911
00:57:41.139 --> 00:57:43.529
The bloody bastards
have shot me in the ass!


912
00:57:43.529 --> 00:57:45.396
Take cover, men.

913
00:57:45.396 --> 00:57:48.003
If it's prayers he wants,
he can make up his own.


914
00:58:23.499 --> 00:58:25.410
<i>Oh, Jesus.</i>

915
00:58:25.410 --> 00:58:27.366
<i>I shouldn't have
been there at all.</i>


916
00:58:27.366 --> 00:58:28.886
<i>Or that poor
Bavarian, either.</i>


917
00:58:31.319 --> 00:58:32.970
<i>For all I know,</i>

918
00:58:32.970 --> 00:58:35.881
<i>we might have been friends.</i>

919
00:58:36.358 --> 00:58:37.837
<i>Instead of him dead,</i>

920
00:58:38.271 --> 00:58:40.269
<i>out there in the mud.</i>

921
00:58:40.269 --> 00:58:43.397
<i>And me, lying here like...</i>

922
00:58:43.397 --> 00:58:46.394
<i>like some freak
in a carnival show.</i>


923
00:58:49.175 --> 00:58:51.217
<i>Remember that time
in Los Angeles,</i>


924
00:58:51.217 --> 00:58:52.782
<i>when we all went
to the circus,</i>


925
00:58:52.782 --> 00:58:54.824
<i>and took Kareen
with us, too?</i>


926
00:58:54.824 --> 00:58:56.648
<i>And when we got
home, the old man began</i>

927
00:58:56.648 --> 00:58:58.951
<i>imitating those
sideshow barkers?</i>


928
00:58:58.951 --> 00:59:01.383
<i>And the rest of us
joined in, too?</i>


929
00:59:02.904 --> 00:59:04.903
<i>He was a funny man!</i>

930
00:59:04.903 --> 00:59:07.987
<i>Just think what he
could have done with me,</i>


931
00:59:07.987 --> 00:59:09.465
<i>the way I am now.</i>

932
00:59:09.465 --> 00:59:12.810
<i>I eat...through a tube!</i>

933
00:59:13.159 --> 00:59:16.372
He breathes through a tube.

934
00:59:16.372 --> 00:59:18.980
And whatever goes in a tube

935
00:59:18.980 --> 00:59:21.065
has to come out
through a tube.


936
00:59:21.587 --> 00:59:25.235
He is the armless,
legless wonder


937
00:59:25.235 --> 00:59:27.321
of the 20th century!

938
00:59:27.321 --> 00:59:28.885
And yet, by God,

939
00:59:28.885 --> 00:59:30.971
he's just as alive
as you and me!


940
00:59:30.971 --> 00:59:35.141
He was a good boy.

941
00:59:35.402 --> 00:59:39.313
He was always forgetting things!

942
00:59:39.313 --> 00:59:41.485
And it's this
fellow right here!


943
00:59:41.485 --> 00:59:45.091
But he don't worry
about no shoes.


944
00:59:45.091 --> 00:59:46.481
'Cause he don't
need no shoes!


945
00:59:46.742 --> 00:59:48.914
He'd forget his overshoes.

946
00:59:48.914 --> 00:59:51.521
No shoes! No shirt!

947
00:59:51.521 --> 00:59:53.084
No socks!

948
00:59:53.084 --> 00:59:55.169
No gloves! No hat!

949
00:59:55.169 --> 00:59:57.255
He would forget his cap.

950
00:59:57.604 --> 00:59:59.255
No necktie!
No collar buttons!


951
00:59:59.255 --> 01:00:00.297
No vest! No coat!
No nothing!


952
01:00:00.818 --> 01:00:02.903
And now...

953
01:00:02.903 --> 01:00:07.075
he's forgotten...
just everything.


954
01:00:07.075 --> 01:00:10.203
All you gotta do
is drop a love offering


955
01:00:10.203 --> 01:00:13.939
of 15 cents or more
in this little lady's thunder mug.


956
01:00:14.244 --> 01:00:16.242
And I'll you
what I'm gonna do!


957
01:00:16.242 --> 01:00:19.067
I'm gonna lift the lid
of this box here,


958
01:00:19.067 --> 01:00:21.673
and I'm gonna let you
look at the face


959
01:00:21.673 --> 01:00:23.801
of the only man in the world

960
01:00:23.801 --> 01:00:27.452
who don't give a damn
about anything.


961
01:00:27.452 --> 01:00:29.537
And remember!

962
01:00:29.537 --> 01:00:32.143
It only cost ya 15 cents.

963
01:00:32.143 --> 01:00:34.229
And if this guy
looks back at you,


964
01:00:34.229 --> 01:00:35.793
by golly, I'll give ya
a five dollar bill.


965
01:00:37.704 --> 01:00:39.876
All right! Bring on
the music, Rollo Boy!


966
01:00:39.876 --> 01:00:41.440
Okay! Step right up!

967
01:00:41.962 --> 01:00:43.526
Step right up, folks!

968
01:00:43.526 --> 01:00:45.611
Step right up. Hurry,
hurry, hurry. hurry.


969
01:00:45.611 --> 01:00:47.219
Get a close look
at the man who can't--


970
01:00:47.740 --> 01:00:51.389
Thank you.
Or maybe he can!


971
01:00:51.389 --> 01:00:55.040
Thank you.

972
01:00:56.602 --> 01:00:58.167
Thank you.

973
01:01:00.253 --> 01:01:02.860
See that little lady?
Make her pot ring out


974
01:01:02.860 --> 01:01:04.945
like the bells of St. Mary!

975
01:01:05.466 --> 01:01:08.073
Glory, glory, glory!
Thank you, sir.


976
01:01:08.073 --> 01:01:10.159
Thank you.

977
01:01:10.680 --> 01:01:12.244
Thank you.

978
01:01:12.287 --> 01:01:13.852
Thank you!

979
01:01:16.979 --> 01:01:19.586
Thank you.

980
01:01:19.586 --> 01:01:22.062
Thank you.

981
01:01:26.017 --> 01:01:27.579
<i>Thank you.</i>

982
01:01:44.872 --> 01:01:46.957
<i>What's this?</i>

983
01:01:46.957 --> 01:01:49.477
