inside out ♪


1300
01:26:57.713 --> 01:27:01.275
♪ Till the boys come ♪

1301
01:27:01.275 --> 01:27:05.966
♪ Home ♪

1302
01:27:16.133 --> 01:27:17.090
Father.

1303
01:27:24.171 --> 01:27:25.256
Hello, son.

1304
01:27:25.256 --> 01:27:26.256
Hello, Father.

1305
01:27:26.778 --> 01:27:28.342
Want some honey?

1306
01:27:28.342 --> 01:27:29.385
No, thanks.

1307
01:27:29.385 --> 01:27:30.428
Sit down.

1308
01:27:37.639 --> 01:27:39.202
Goodbye, Joe.

1309
01:27:39.202 --> 01:27:41.201
Who was that girl?

1310
01:27:44.155 --> 01:27:45.677
I really don't know.

1311
01:27:47.241 --> 01:27:48.761
I was fishing.
She happened by.


1312
01:27:49.283 --> 01:27:51.367
Wriggled
into my arms and stayed there.


1313
01:27:52.846 --> 01:27:54.931
So many young girls
these days


1314
01:27:54.931 --> 01:27:59.057
seem to be
hunting for a place in old men's arms.


1315
01:27:59.057 --> 01:28:00.015
Pshew.

1316
01:28:02.099 --> 01:28:03.664
Where did all
the young men go?


1317
01:28:03.664 --> 01:28:05.140
They drift away.

1318
01:28:06.704 --> 01:28:08.312
How is it with you,
Father?


1319
01:28:08.312 --> 01:28:09.789
It's all right.

1320
01:28:11.309 --> 01:28:13.351
You know,
it's a funny thing.


1321
01:28:16.262 --> 01:28:18.348
I was a very good
shoe clerk.


1322
01:28:18.348 --> 01:28:19.912
But I was
more than that.


1323
01:28:19.912 --> 01:28:21.476
I could handle
a horse.


1324
01:28:21.476 --> 01:28:22.519
If I had a cow,

1325
01:28:22.519 --> 01:28:24.039
she was
always healthy,


1326
01:28:24.039 --> 01:28:25.647
gave plenty of milk.

1327
01:28:25.647 --> 01:28:28.254
Raised our own food
on two city lots.


1328
01:28:29.818 --> 01:28:32.860
Even up to the honey
on our biscuits.


1329
01:28:33.902 --> 01:28:36.509
I could, uh, hoe
a pretty good row...


1330
01:28:37.898 --> 01:28:39.376
lay out
a pretty good grade


1331
01:28:39.376 --> 01:28:41.983
on an uphill road.
Build a house.


1332
01:28:44.069 --> 01:28:47.196
But I never did learn
how to make any money.


1333
01:28:47.630 --> 01:28:50.717
The goddamndest thing
I ever ran into.


1334
01:28:52.279 --> 01:28:53.757
See, the trouble
with life is


1335
01:28:53.757 --> 01:28:55.320
you work so much,
you don't enjoy it.


1336
01:28:55.320 --> 01:28:56.885
Yeah.

1337
01:28:56.885 --> 01:28:57.927
Yeah.

1338
01:29:01.534 --> 01:29:02.619
Better this way.

1339
01:29:04.705 --> 01:29:05.226
Except...

1340
01:29:07.312 --> 01:29:08.353
I do miss your mother.

1341
01:29:13.004 --> 01:29:14.047
How is she?

1342
01:29:14.047 --> 01:29:16.133
I haven't seen her lately.

1343
01:29:16.133 --> 01:29:17.174
Oh.

1344
01:29:18.217 --> 01:29:19.260
Well...

1345
01:29:22.735 --> 01:29:24.734
not too long
till sunrise.


1346
01:29:24.734 --> 01:29:26.298
Mmhh.

1347
01:29:26.298 --> 01:29:27.819
I have to go.

1348
01:29:29.904 --> 01:29:31.337
Trout'll be rising.

1349
01:29:31.337 --> 01:29:33.248
Willow Lake.

1350
01:29:33.248 --> 01:29:35.204
Now that I got
my pole back, I don't want to miss 'em.


1351
01:29:38.854 --> 01:29:40.375
Goodbye, Father.

1352
01:29:42.982 --> 01:29:45.024
Give my love
to your mother when you see her.


1353
01:29:47.065 --> 01:29:49.020
Sorry I had to leave
you in the lurch,


1354
01:29:49.063 --> 01:29:50.628
but it was
the only way, believe me.


1355
01:29:52.193 --> 01:29:53.060
Goodbye.

1356
01:30:24.168 --> 01:30:26.731
Joe.

1357
01:30:26.731 --> 01:30:28.731
Joe.

1358
01:30:28.731 --> 01:30:31.077
Here I am.

1359
01:30:31.077 --> 01:30:33.074
No, Joe.
Over here.


1360
01:30:34.638 --> 01:30:36.724
Let's play
blindman's bluff.


1361
01:30:37.767 --> 01:30:38.810
Joe.

1362
01:30:43.936 --> 01:30:45.936
Find me, Joe.

1363
01:30:45.936 --> 01:30:48.454
Why did you
leave me, Joe?


1364
01:30:49.497 --> 01:30:50.498
Run, Joe.

1365
01:30:50.498 --> 01:30:53.365
Why didn't you
write me?


1366
01:30:53.365 --> 01:30:54.711
I couldn't
write you!


1367
01:30:54.711 --> 01:30:56.275
I just couldn't!

1368
01:30:58.230 --> 01:30:59.230
Why couldn't you?

1369
01:30:59.230 --> 01:31:00.706
I can't tell you!

1370
01:31:00.706 --> 01:31:02.270
That's all!
I can't!


1371
01:31:02.270 --> 01:31:05.225
You don't
love me, Joe.


1372
01:31:10.265 --> 01:31:13.828
You don't love me.

1373
01:31:13.828 --> 01:31:15.392
I do love you!

1374
01:31:16.825 --> 01:31:17.910
I do love you!

1375
01:31:17.910 --> 01:31:19.953
No, you don't, Joe.
You never did.


1376
01:31:19.953 --> 01:31:22.039
Don't go, Kareen!

1377
01:31:23.604 --> 01:31:25.079
Where are you?

1378
01:31:25.079 --> 01:31:27.209
Olly olly
oxen free!


1379
01:31:28.599 --> 01:31:30.163
Don't go away
from me again.


1380
01:31:36.767 --> 01:31:38.287
Please.

1381
01:31:39.287 --> 01:31:40.329
Don't.

1382
01:31:45.977 --> 01:31:47.020
You need help, son.

1383
01:31:50.149 --> 01:31:53.797
There isn't any help.

1384
01:31:53.797 --> 01:31:56.970
Have you asked for any?

1385
01:31:56.970 --> 01:31:58.534
I can't.

1386
01:32:02.183 --> 01:32:04.269
I can't ask for anything.

1387
01:32:04.790 --> 01:32:08.440
There is no way
I can talk to them.


1388
01:32:08.440 --> 01:32:12.089
Then why don't you
send a telegram?


1389
01:32:23.906 --> 01:32:26.556
A telegram?

1390
01:32:26.556 --> 01:32:29.119
Don't you remember
when you were little?


1391
01:32:29.119 --> 01:32:31.205
How you and Bill Harper
used to


1392
01:32:31.205 --> 01:32:33.291
string a wire
between the two houses


1393
01:32:33.291 --> 01:32:35.767
so you could telegraph
to each other?


1394
01:32:37.375 --> 01:32:39.242
Yes.

1395
01:32:46.150 --> 01:32:47.715
Still remember
the Morse code?


1396
01:32:49.235 --> 01:32:50.800
Yes.

1397
01:32:53.840 --> 01:32:57.011
What good is that?

1398
01:32:57.011 --> 01:32:59.575
How can I type out
a message to them?


1399
01:32:59.575 --> 01:33:02.139
You've got to learn to think.

1400
01:33:02.139 --> 01:33:04.224
Use your head.

1401
01:33:06.266 --> 01:33:08.698
Yes.

1402
01:33:08.698 --> 01:33:11.784
Yes. My head.

1403
01:33:13.782 --> 01:33:16.216
My head. My head, my head!

1404
01:33:16.737 --> 01:33:18.474
Yes.

1405
01:33:19.865 --> 01:33:23.515
<i>Yes. My head.</i>

1406
01:33:23.515 --> 01:33:25.600
<i>My head.</i>

1407
01:33:49.886 --> 01:33:51.972
<i>Where is she going?</i>

1408
01:33:53.796 --> 01:33:56.968
Captain?
Yes?


1409
01:33:56.968 --> 01:33:59.053
Could you come here
a minute, please?


1410
01:33:59.053 --> 01:34:02.659
Yes, of course. Would you
take care of that, nurse? Thank you.


1411
01:34:02.659 --> 01:34:04.745
<i>She's brought somebody in!</i>

1412
01:34:13.043 --> 01:34:15.128
I can't understand
what he's doing.


1413
01:34:16.648 --> 01:34:18.213
May I see
the orders, please?


1414
01:34:18.213 --> 01:34:19.777
Yes.

1415
01:34:21.341 --> 01:34:23.947
Thank you.

1416
01:34:23.947 --> 01:34:26.380
Probably an early entry.

1417
01:34:29.944 --> 01:34:31.463
"If bodily action
becomes violent


1418
01:34:31.985 --> 01:34:33.897
or persistently repetitive"--

1419
01:34:33.897 --> 01:34:36.981
These movements
are persistently repetitive.


1420
01:34:36.981 --> 01:34:39.588
"They must be treated
as reflexive muscular spasms."


1421
01:34:39.588 --> 01:34:42.239
Which is to say by sedation.

1422
01:34:42.760 --> 01:34:44.846
Fair enough.
I'll prepare an injection.


1423
01:34:46.931 --> 01:34:48.886
<i>Why is she trying to stop me?</i>

1424
01:34:49.450 --> 01:34:52.579
I don't believe that
the movement is reflexive.


1425
01:34:54.012 --> 01:34:56.055
Oh, you don't?

1426
01:34:56.055 --> 01:34:59.053
Well, General Tillery
will pass through on the 23rd


1427
01:34:59.053 --> 01:35:02.093
with his annual
staff inspection.


1428
01:35:02.093 --> 01:35:03.571
If you don't trust me,
nurse,


1429
01:35:03.571 --> 01:35:05.657
perhaps you'd better
take it up with him.


1430
01:35:09.349 --> 01:35:10.914
I will.

1431
01:35:10.914 --> 01:35:13.521
Well, that's excellent,
nurse.


1432
01:35:13.521 --> 01:35:16.649
General Tillery is
the chief operating surgeon


1433
01:35:16.649 --> 01:35:18.734
who wrote those orders.

1434
01:35:20.254 --> 01:35:21.818
<i>No. No.</i>

1435
01:35:22.339 --> 01:35:24.425
<i>Don't give me dope.</i>

1436
01:35:24.425 --> 01:35:27.553
<i>Don't put me under again.
Would you unlock the door, please?</i>


1437
01:35:27.553 --> 01:35:30.682
<i>I'm trying to talk to you.</i>

1438
01:35:31.203 --> 01:35:34.851
<i>Oh, God, please
make them hear me.</i>


1439
01:35:34.851 --> 01:35:38.372
<i>All I'm asking is for you
to take one little idea</i>


1440
01:35:38.372 --> 01:35:41.934
<i>that's in my mind
and put it into their minds.</i>


1441
01:35:41.934 --> 01:35:45.062
<i>Maybe only 2 or 3
feet away from me.</i>


1442
01:35:45.062 --> 01:35:49.015
<i>It's-- It's such
a little thing to ask,</i>


1443
01:35:49.015 --> 01:35:51.101
<i>but they won't listen.</i>

1444
01:35:51.101 --> 01:35:53.186
<i>They won't hear me.</i>

1445
01:35:53.186 --> 01:35:56.314
<i>All they do is give me dope,</i>

1446
01:35:56.314 --> 01:35:58.749
<i>and I go down</i>

1447
01:35:58.749 --> 01:36:01.355
<i>and down</i>

1448
01:36:01.355 --> 01:36:02.918
<i>and...</i>

1449
01:36:03.440 --> 01:36:05.004
<i>Oh, there you are, brothers.</i>

1450
01:36:06.481 --> 01:36:09.609
<i>What were you hunting
when they caught you?</i>


1451
01:36:09.609 --> 01:36:12.781
<i>Look, Father!
I found your fishing pole!</i>


1452
01:36:14.823 --> 01:36:17.604
<i>Use your head, son.</i>

1453
01:36:17.604 --> 01:36:20.557
<i>I am, Father. I am.</i>

1454
01:36:21.861 --> 01:36:24.468
<i>Hear me.</i>

1455
01:36:24.468 --> 01:36:28.986
<i>Please try to understand
what I'm doing and hear me!</i>


1456
01:36:41.541 --> 01:36:43.627
<i>She did hear me!</i>

1457
01:36:43.627 --> 01:36:45.582
<i>She's going
to get somebody!</i>


1458
01:36:48.103 --> 01:36:50.405
<i>She didn't even
close the door!</i>


1459
01:36:58.704 --> 01:37:01.136
<i>I've broken through.</i>

1460
01:37:01.136 --> 01:37:04.308
<i>I'm back
with people again.</i>


1461
01:37:04.308 --> 01:37:07.437
<i>Hello,
all you people out there.</i>


1462
01:37:07.437 --> 01:37:11.563
<i>It's me, and we're going
to talk to each other.</i>


1463
01:37:11.563 --> 01:37:14.170
<i>They're here. 
A lot of them.</i>

1464
01:37:21.253 --> 01:37:22.729
It's Morse code.

1465
01:37:22.729 --> 01:37:24.510
For what?

1466
01:37:24.771 --> 01:37:28.290
SOS. Help.

1467
01:37:32.374 --> 01:37:35.328
Do you mean to say
that this man


1468
01:37:35.328 --> 01:37:38.848
is actually speaking to us?

1469
01:37:38.848 --> 01:37:41.281
<i>What are they doing?</i>

1470
01:37:41.281 --> 01:37:42.757
Yes, sir.

1471
01:37:51.838 --> 01:37:53.879
Decerebrated, General?

1472
01:37:54.879 --> 01:37:57.920
Completely decerebrated?

1473
01:37:57.920 --> 01:37:59.962
<i>What are they waiting for?</i>

1474
01:38:00.180 --> 01:38:01.223
<i>What's happening?</i>

1475
01:38:10.997 --> 01:38:13.604
<i>Are they leaving?</i>

1476
01:38:13.604 --> 01:38:15.168
<i>No.</i>

1477
01:38:15.168 --> 01:38:17.776
<i>Just one of them.</i>

1478
01:38:17.776 --> 01:38:19.774
<i>Or maybe two.</i>

1479
01:38:19.774 --> 01:38:21.381
<i>No. Just one.</i>

1480
01:38:27.507 --> 01:38:29.420
Ask what he wants.

1481
01:38:29.420 --> 01:38:32.373
How can I ask a man like this
a question like that?


1482
01:38:32.373 --> 01:38:36.457
By asking it.
How else can we help him?


1483
01:38:37.413 --> 01:38:41.019
<i>Why don't they do something?</i>

1484
01:38:43.452 --> 01:38:44.930
<i>They are.
What...</i>


1485
01:38:47.840 --> 01:38:52.185
do...you...

1486
01:38:54.531 --> 01:38:56.225
want?

1487
01:38:58.137 --> 01:39:01.569
<i>What do I want?</i>

1488
01:39:02.003 --> 01:39:03.654
<i>What do I want?</i>

1489
01:39:05.350 --> 01:39:07.218
<i>What I want...</i>

1490
01:39:09.303 --> 01:39:10.867
<i>I want out!</i>

1491
01:39:11.258 --> 01:39:12.648
<i>I want to feel fresh air
against my skin.</i>


1492
01:39:12.952 --> 01:39:15.342
<i>I want to feel people
around me.</i>


1493
01:39:15.646 --> 01:39:17.645
<i>No.</i>

1494
01:39:17.645 --> 01:39:18.688
<i>It would cost too much money</i>

1495
01:39:19.209 --> 01:39:20.685
<i>taking care of me
on the outside.</i>


1496
01:39:20.685 --> 01:39:22.554
<i>They never do that.</i>

1497
01:39:22.554 --> 01:39:25.074
<i>But-- But maybe
there's a way</i>


1498
01:39:25.074 --> 01:39:27.159
<i>I can take care of myself.</i>

1499
01:39:28.724 --> 01:39:31.242
<i>Yes! There is a way!</i>

1500
01:39:31.242 --> 01:39:33.328
<i>All you have to do
is put me on display</i>


1501
01:39:33.328 --> 01:39:34.935
<i>and people
will pay to see me.</i>


1502
01:39:34.935 --> 01:39:37.021
<i>Lots of people.
Put me in a fancy coffin</i>


1503
01:39:37.542 --> 01:39:39.497
<i>with windows in it,
and take me out where people</i>


1504
01:39:39.497 --> 01:39:41.453
<i>are spending money
and having fun.</i>


1505
01:39:41.453 --> 01:39:43.539
<i>Take me to the beaches
and the county fairs</i>


1506
01:39:43.539 --> 01:39:44.580
<i>and the 4th of July
celebrations</i>


1507
01:39:44.580 --> 01:39:46.666
<i>and all the church bazaars.</i>

1508
01:39:46.666 --> 01:39:48.708
<i>They've seen
the pin-headed girl from Timbuktu</i>


1509
01:39:48.708 --> 01:39:49.751
<i>or the dog-faced man</i>

1510
01:39:49.751 --> 01:39:51.315
<i>who crawls on his belly
like a reptile.</i>


1511
01:39:51.315 --> 01:39:53.357
<i>But they're not real freaks.
They were born that way.</i>


1512
01:39:53.357 --> 01:39:55.442
<i>They were made
that way by God.</i>


1513
01:39:55.442 --> 01:39:57.528
<i>But this thing here
in his fancy coffin</i>


1514
01:39:57.528 --> 01:39:59.569
<i>was made by people--</i>

1515
01:39:59.569 --> 01:40:01.655
<i>by you and me
and the lady next door--</i>


1516
01:40:01.655 --> 01:40:03.132
<i>and that takes
a lot of planning</i>


1517
01:40:03.132 --> 01:40:04.610
<i>and costs a lot of money.</i>

1518
01:40:04.610 --> 01:40:06.694
<i>Advertise me as the only
piece of meat in the world</i>


1519
01:40:07.216 --> 01:40:08.780
<i>that can talk through
the back of its head.</i>


1520
01:40:08.780 --> 01:40:11.301
<i>And if that
doesn't pull them in, then-- then-- then--</i>


1521
01:40:11.866 --> 01:40:13.951
<i>then bill me as the last man
on earth who joined the Army.</i>


1522
01:40:13.951 --> 01:40:16.036
<i>Because the army makes men.</i>

1523
01:40:16.036 --> 01:40:17.600
<i>So rally around
the flag, boys--</i>


1524
01:40:17.600 --> 01:40:19.686
<i>your flag, their flag,
anybody's flag--</i>


1525
01:40:19.686 --> 01:40:20.641
<i>because the flag
needs soldiers,</i>


1526
01:40:20.641 --> 01:40:23.683
<i>and the army makes men.</i>

1527
01:40:23.683 --> 01:40:28.896
I...want...out...

1528
01:40:29.157 --> 01:40:32.241
so...people...

1529
01:40:32.762 --> 01:40:36.151
can...see...

1530
01:40:36.151 --> 01:40:39.019
what...I am.

1531
01:40:39.019 --> 01:40:43.450
Put me...in...

1532
01:40:43.450 --> 01:40:46.839
a...

1533
01:40:46.839 --> 01:40:50.879
c-carnival...show

1534
01:40:50.879 --> 01:40:55.008
where they...can

1535
01:40:55.051 --> 01:40:57.614
look...at me.

1536
01:40:57.614 --> 01:41:00.785
Let...me out.

1537
01:41:00.785 --> 01:41:04.869
Well, what could we
have expected?


1538
01:41:05.912 --> 01:41:08.475
Tell him, uh...

1539
01:41:08.475 --> 01:41:10.473
Tell him we'll do
everything we can,


1540
01:41:10.473 --> 01:41:13.385
but, uh, his condition
won't permit him to be moved.


1541
01:41:13.688 --> 01:41:15.123
For the present, that is.

1542
01:41:15.644 --> 01:41:18.468
Be sure to say
"for the present."


1543
01:41:27.853 --> 01:41:29.286
If...

1544
01:41:30.893 --> 01:41:31.893
you...

1545
01:41:34.326 --> 01:41:38.237
won't...let...

1546
01:41:38.540 --> 01:41:41.495
people see me,

1547
01:41:41.669 --> 01:41:43.190
then...

1548
01:41:45.274 --> 01:41:46.622
kill me.

1549
01:42:01.132 --> 01:42:04.129
He's upset.
Understandably so.


1550
01:42:04.650 --> 01:42:06.215
Ask him what his name is.

1551
01:42:26.592 --> 01:42:29.937
These shutters are to be closed
at all times.


1552
01:42:29.937 --> 01:42:32.022
What's he saying?

1553
01:42:32.457 --> 01:42:35.063
He says, "Kill me."

1554
01:42:35.063 --> 01:42:37.497
Over and over again.
"Kill me."


1555
01:42:41.364 --> 01:42:44.839
Tell him we'll do everything
we can to make him comfortable.

1556
01:42:44.839 --> 01:42:46.360
For now, he needs rest.

1557
01:42:46.360 --> 01:42:49.357
Tell him we'll give him
a sedative and come back later.


1558
01:42:49.357 --> 01:42:51.400
And try to get his name.

1559
01:42:53.441 --> 01:42:56.440
You're not to mention
what has happened here to anyone.


1560
01:42:56.440 --> 01:42:59.481
I'll hold you collectively
responsible for any breach.


1561
01:42:59.481 --> 01:43:02.522
If new orders are received
in view of the new situation which has developed,


1562
01:43:02.522 --> 01:43:04.607
you'll be notified.

1563
01:43:05.129 --> 01:43:06.170
Well?

1564
01:43:08.213 --> 01:43:11.123
He won't wait
for an answer.


1565
01:43:11.123 --> 01:43:14.210
All he says is

1566
01:43:14.210 --> 01:43:18.640
"Kill me, kill me, kill me."

1567
01:43:21.116 --> 01:43:24.201
Don't you have some message
for him, Padre?


1568
01:43:26.722 --> 01:43:27.677
You could at least tell him

1569
01:43:27.677 --> 01:43:29.370
to put his faith in God,
couldn't you?


1570
01:43:30.805 --> 01:43:33.369
I'll pray for him
for the rest of my days,


1571
01:43:33.889 --> 01:43:36.323
but I will not risk
testing his faith


1572
01:43:36.323 --> 01:43:38.191
against your stupidity.

1573
01:43:42.840 --> 01:43:44.881
Well, you're a hell
of a priest, aren't you?


1574
01:43:45.403 --> 01:43:48.488
He's the product
of your profession,


1575
01:43:48.488 --> 01:43:50.877
not mine.

1576
01:43:52.920 --> 01:43:55.092
Clear the room.

1577
01:43:55.092 --> 01:43:57.698
Give him a light sedative,
nurse.


1578
01:43:59.262 --> 01:44:01.869
<i>They're going away. Why?</i>

1579
01:44:01.869 --> 01:44:03.868
<i>Why don't they get it
over with and kill me?</i>


1580
01:44:05.345 --> 01:44:07.735
<i>But you're still here.</i>

1581
01:44:07.735 --> 01:44:10.341
<i>Can't you see
what I'm tapping to you?</i>


1582
01:44:10.341 --> 01:44:13.470
<i>I'm asking you to kill me.</i>

1583
01:44:13.470 --> 01:44:15.555
<i>Please do.</i>

1584
01:44:39.928 --> 01:44:41.839
O my God,

1585
01:44:42.839 --> 01:44:45.271
I'm heartily sorry

1586
01:44:45.271 --> 01:44:47.748
for having offended thee.

1587
01:44:49.227 --> 01:44:52.266
And I detest all my sins,

1588
01:44:52.266 --> 01:44:54.700
not because of Thy judgment,
O Lord,


1589
01:44:54.700 --> 01:44:57.524
but because
thou art all good


1590
01:44:57.524 --> 01:45:00.781
and deserving
of all my love.


1591
01:45:08.037 --> 01:45:10.123
I firmly resolve,

1592
01:45:10.123 --> 01:45:13.511
with the help of thy grace,

1593
01:45:13.511 --> 01:45:16.945
to sin no more, to avoid
all the occasions of sin.


1594
01:45:19.942 --> 01:45:21.462
Amen.

1595
01:45:28.848 --> 01:45:30.890
<i>Oh, nurse--</i>

1596
01:45:30.890 --> 01:45:35.017
<i>beautiful,
beautiful nurse--</i>


1597
01:45:35.017 --> 01:45:37.017
<i>thank you,</i>

1598
01:45:37.017 --> 01:45:40.492
<i>thank you, thank you.</i>

1599
01:45:40.492 --> 01:45:42.577
<i>Dear God,
thank her for me.</i>


1600
01:45:42.577 --> 01:45:44.663
<i>Be sweet to her, God.</i>

1601
01:45:44.663 --> 01:45:47.183
<i>Make her happy.
Make her beautiful.</i>


1602
01:45:47.183 --> 01:45:49.834
<i>Make everything she wants
come true!</i>


1603
01:45:50.355 --> 01:45:51.919
<i>Make everyone love her!</i>

1604
01:45:54.004 --> 01:45:55.568
No!

1605
01:45:57.132 --> 01:45:58.653
No.

1606
01:45:58.653 --> 01:45:59.695
Leave the room.

1607
01:45:59.695 --> 01:46:04.083
<i>Oh, somebody stopped her.</i>

1608
01:46:04.083 --> 01:46:06.386
<i>Why?</i>

1609
01:46:06.386 --> 01:46:10.167
I said,
"Leave the room."


1610
01:46:10.688 --> 01:46:12.513
Give me the key.

1611
01:46:12.513 --> 01:46:15.076
<i>What's happening?</i>

1612
01:46:15.076 --> 01:46:17.030
The key?

1613
01:46:20.594 --> 01:46:22.157
Go on.

1614
01:46:24.155 --> 01:46:26.719
<i>She's going.</i>

1615
01:46:26.719 --> 01:46:29.499
<i>I can feel her
moving toward the door.</i>


1616
01:46:29.499 --> 01:46:32.496
<i>He's sending her away.</i>

1617
01:46:32.496 --> 01:46:34.496
<i>Why?</i>

1618
01:46:34.496 --> 01:46:36.494
<i>First they
close the shutters,</i>


1619
01:46:36.494 --> 01:46:40.622
<i>and now they're
sending her away.</i>


1620
01:46:40.622 --> 01:46:43.185
<i>Why did they
close the shutters?</i>


1621
01:46:45.531 --> 01:46:48.137
<i>Why is he
sending her away?</i>


1622
01:46:49.701 --> 01:46:52.787
<i>Why won't they
let me talk?</i>


1623
01:46:53.177 --> 01:46:56.827
<i>Because I'm a secret
or something?</i>


1624
01:46:56.827 --> 01:46:58.913
<i>Oh, I don't know.</i>

1625
01:47:00.432 --> 01:47:02.432
<i>She's gone.</i>

1626
01:47:03.996 --> 01:47:06.082
<i>Good-bye, nurse.</i>

1627
01:47:07.688 --> 01:47:10.295
<i>You're gone,</i>

1628
01:47:10.295 --> 01:47:12.380
<i>and I'm a secret.</i>

1629
01:47:13.945 --> 01:47:16.030
<i>Oh, no. Not that again.</i>

1630
01:47:20.200 --> 01:47:23.807
<i>I-- I thought
they'd be glad</i>


1631
01:47:23.807 --> 01:47:26.848
<i>that I found a way to--</i>

1632
01:47:26.848 --> 01:47:28.934
<i>to talk to them.</i>

1633
01:47:29.976 --> 01:47:32.062
<i>But they're not.</i>

1634
01:47:35.711 --> 01:47:38.839
<i>The only thing on this earth
I'm any good for</i>


1635
01:47:40.361 --> 01:47:43.010
<i>they won't let me do.</i>

1636
01:47:43.531 --> 01:47:44.574
<i>All they want is to push me</i>

1637
01:47:44.574 --> 01:47:48.745
<i>back into the darkness
down here</i>


1638
01:47:48.745 --> 01:47:51.742
<i>so they won't ever
see me again.</i>


1639
01:47:53.177 --> 01:47:56.782
<i>He's gone, too.</i>

1640
01:47:56.782 --> 01:48:00.214
<i>Well, now I know.</i>

1641
01:48:00.214 --> 01:48:02.258
<i>They'll never let me out.</i>

1642
01:48:04.255 --> 01:48:07.774
<i>They'll keep me a secret here
until someday,</i>


1643
01:48:07.774 --> 01:48:10.772
<i>when I'm an old, old man,</i>

1644
01:48:10.772 --> 01:48:13.814
<i>I'll sneak away
from them and die.</i>


1645
01:48:16.421 --> 01:48:17.985
<i>It isn't easy, though.</i>

1646
01:48:19.374 --> 01:48:24.371
<i>Inside me,
I'm screaming and yelling</i>


1647
01:48:24.371 --> 01:48:26.848
<i>and howling
like a trapped animal...</i>


1648
01:48:28.368 --> 01:48:31.844
<i>and nobody
pays any attention.</i>


1649
01:48:31.844 --> 01:48:34.884
<i>If I had arms,
I could kill myself.</i>


1650
01:48:36.363 --> 01:48:39.360
<i>If I had legs,
I could run away.</i>


1651
01:48:39.360 --> 01:48:41.272
<i>If I had a voice,</i>

1652
01:48:41.272 --> 01:48:45.094
<i>I could talk and be some
kind of company for myself.</i>


1653
01:48:45.573 --> 01:48:47.571
<i>I could yell for help.</i>

1654
01:48:48.614 --> 01:48:51.482
<i>But nobody'd help me.</i>

1655
01:48:51.482 --> 01:48:54.479
<i>Not even God,
because there isn't any God.</i>


1656
01:48:54.479 --> 01:48:56.999
<i>Couldn't be
in a place like this.</i>


1657
01:48:58.389 --> 01:49:00.258
<i>And, uh...</i>

1658
01:49:02.213 --> 01:49:04.690
<i>And yet,</i>

1659
01:49:04.690 --> 01:49:08.295
<i>I've just got
to do something</i>


1660
01:49:10.728 --> 01:49:13.813
<i>because I--</i>

1661
01:49:14.768 --> 01:49:17.158
<i>I don't see how I can</i>

1662
01:49:17.158 --> 01:49:19.721
<i>go on like this</i>

1663
01:49:19.721 --> 01:49:22.197
<i>much longer.</i>

1664
01:49:26.325 --> 01:49:29.410
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1665
01:49:30.164 --> 01:49:32.786
<i>Help Me.</i>

1666
01:49:34.170 --> 01:49:37.172
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1667
01:49:38.092 --> 01:49:40.549
<i>Help Me.</i>

1668
01:49:41.848 --> 01:49:44.471
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1669
01:49:45.729 --> 01:49:48.019
<i>Help Me.</i>

1670
01:49:49.484 --> 01:49:52.356
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1671
01:49:53.323 --> 01:49:55.780
<i>Help Me.</i>

1672
01:49:57.329 --> 01:50:00.332
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1673
01:50:01.461 --> 01:50:03.869
<i>Help Me.</i>

1674
01:50:05.133 --> 01:50:08.197
<i>S.O.S.</i>

1675
01:50:09.222 --> 01:50:11.097
<i>Help Me.</i>